title: Bryson remembers MTSU's last win over Vanderbilt
text:
Bryson remembers MTSU's last win over Vanderbilt 
Updated: Thu, Oct 01 2015, 10:55 PM 
Stream WZTV Fox 17 Newscasts LIVE starting with Fox 17 This Morning at 4:30am, News at 5:30pm and News at 9pm & 10 pm 
Ten years ago today. That's the last time Vanderbilt met Middle Tennessee State on the football field. The Blue Raiders won 17-15. 
In fact, MTSU has won all three times the two teams have gotten together as FBS opponents. A frightening fact for Vandy fans. A thrilling one for Blue Raider rooters. 
Jeremiah Bryson was in the stands 10-years ago when the Blue Raiders blocked Vanderbilt's bid for a last second victory. The former Smyrna star and MTSU running back doesn't remember a whole lot about that game. 
But that doesn't mean he isn't pumped to be part of it now!
